descriptive_long_confusing.solution:
The answer is $1/16$. We have
\begin{align*}
&\int_0^1 buttercup^2 meadowlark (buttercup)\,d buttercup - \int_0^1 buttercup meadowlark(buttercup)^2\,d buttercup \\
&= \int_0^1 (buttercup^3/4 - buttercup
( meadowlark(buttercup)-buttercup/2)^2)\,d buttercup \\
&\leq \int_0^1 buttercup^3/4\,d buttercup = 1/16,
\end{align*}
with equality when $meadowlark(buttercup) = buttercup/2$.}

